<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,592,979]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,418,844,871]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
The habitats of this species has been scenario of several socio-environmental conflicts and the native forest have been replaced and fragmented by avocado crops, urbanization and wildfires (
<bibRefCitation author="Carranza, D. M. &amp; Varas-Belemmi, K. &amp; De Veer, D. &amp; Iglesias-Muller, C. &amp; Coral-Santacruz, D. &amp; Mendez, F. A. &amp; Torres-Lagos, E. &amp; Squeo, F. A. &amp; Gaymer, C. F." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="46 - 59" refId="ref125609" refString="Carranza, D. M., Varas-Belemmi, K., De Veer, D., Iglesias-Muller, C., Coral-Santacruz, D., Mendez, F. A., Torres-Lagos, E., Squeo, F. A. &amp; Gaymer, C. F. (2020) Socio-environmental conflicts: An underestimated threat to biodiversity conservation in Chile. Environmental Science &amp; Policy, 110, 46 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. envsci. 2020.04.006" type="journal article" year="2020">
Carranza 
<emphasis box="[1373,1430,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). All basic aspects of its biology and ecology remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,592,979]" box="[199,1338,952,979]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,952,979]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Conservation status.</emphasis>
EN under B2ab (iii) using AOO = 
<quantity box="[837,894,952,979]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[894,902,952,966]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">2</superScript>
and two localities and subpopulations.
</paragraph>
